Overall, this is a pretty decent spot. Read more for a much more detailed review.  As we arrived, we were told the credit card machine was not working and it's "cash only". While not unusual for hookah spots around bay ridge, I have a feeling the machine is always "broken". So definitely bring cash.  When we got there, only 3 or so tables were taken. Waitress was nice and let us pick whichever table we wanted. Sat down, were greeted with good service.  This place has great food and pretty good hookah.  Now, there are a couple of things that are negative about this place...  1. If you order food, it is VERY UNCOMFORTABLE to eat it. Especially if you order something that can drip. Tables are low coffee tables that aren't really meant for food. Gyro was VERY GOOD, but my fiancee had it drip luckily mostly missing her. I feel like it would be a good idea for the owner to have a couple of full size tables for people that are hungry.  2. This is more of a personal pet peeve. This place adds an automatic 18% gratuities. I feel like adding that to a table of 2 is tacky. Not to mention, waitress really lost out on tips because of that (at least from me). If you want to autograt 4-6 person table... umm ok. But to do that to everyone is just a bit weird.
